		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />After cleaning the &quot;strips&quot; with isopropyl alcohol (not much to it -- I actually just used my finger) and letting the little plastic doo-dad with the metal &quot;legs&quot; soak for about 30 minutes, the microphone slider works correctly once more.  Or maybe it was due to me adjusting the actual microphone a bit?  Really don't know.  Either way, it's working when it wasn't before.  :-)<br /><br />Now to figure out if it's possible to replace the cartridge connector with a new one so I can end the shove-cardboard-behind-the-cartridge method.  Heh.  :-)

		

		</td>
